  "A logistic solution satisfies lim (t->infinity) P(t) = K. If P(t) = 400/(1 + 7e^(-0.6t)), what is K?": "如果P(t) = 400/(1+ 7e(-0.6t)),什么是K?",
  "400": "400 400( 400)",
  "7": "7 7,7",
  "0.6": "0.6",
  "2800": "28000800",
  "As t approaches infinity, e^(-0.6t) approaches 0, so P approaches 400/(1+0) = 400. Therefore K = 400.": "至于无限, e(-0.6t) 接近0, 所以P 接近400/(1+0) = 400。 因此K = 400。",
  "Convert dP/dt = 3P - 0.006P^2 to standard logistic form and identify r and K.": "将dP/dt = 3P - 0.006P2转换为标准后勤表格,并识别r和K。",
  "r = 0.006, K = 3": "r =0.006,K = 3",
  "r = 3, K = 500": "r = 3, K = 500",
  "r = 6, K = 500": "r = 6, K = 500",
  "r = 3, K = 0.006": "r = 3, K =0.006",
  "Factor: dP/dt = 3P(1 - 0.002P) = 3P(1 - P/500). So r = 3 and K = 1/0.002 = 500.": "系数:dP/dt = 3P(1 - 0.0002P) = 3P(1 - P/500)。 所以 r = 3 和 K = 1/0.002 = 500。",
  "What is the standard form of the logistic differential equation?": "后勤差别方程式的标准形式是什么?",
  "dP/dt = rP(1 - P/K), where r is the intrinsic growth rate and K is the carrying capacity": "dP/dt = rP(1 - P/K),r为内在增长率,K为承载能力",
  "dP/dt = rP^2(1 - P/K)": "dP/dt = rP22(1 - P/K)",
  "dP/dt = K - P, where K is the carrying capacity": "dP/dt = K-P, K是承载能力",
  "dP/dt = rP, where r is the growth rate": "dP/dt=rP=rP,其中r为增长率",
  "The standard logistic differential equation is dP/dt = rP(1 - P/K). The term rP represents exponential growth and (1 - P/K) is the logistic correction that slows growth as P approaches K.": "标准后勤差价方程式是dP/dt = rP(1-P/K), \" rP \" 表示指数增长, \" (1-P/K)表示随着P接近K而减缓增长的后勤纠正。",
  "What is the 'logistic solution' formula?": "什么是“逻辑解决方案”公式?",
  "P(t) = P_0 * e^(rt)": "P(t) = P_0 * e__(rt)",
  "P(t) = K + Ae^(-rt)": "P(t) = K + Ae(- t)",
  "P(t) = K(1 - e^(-rt))": "P(t) = K(1 - e__(-rt))",
  "P(t) = K/(1 + Ae^(-rt)), where A = (K - P_0)/P_0": "P(t) = K/(1 + Ae(- t)), 其中 A = (K - P_ 0)/ P_ 0",
  "The explicit solution of the logistic equation is P(t) = K/(1 + Ae^(-rt)), where A is determined by the initial condition: A = (K - P_0)/P_0. As t increases, P approaches K.": "后勤方程式的明确解决办法是P(t) = K/(1+Ae(-rt)),其中A由初始条件确定:A = (K-P_0)/P_0。",
  "What does 'partial fraction decomposition' mean in solving the logistic equation?": "\"部分分解\"在解答后勤方程式中意味着什么?",
  "A method for numerical integration according to widely held views on this topic": "根据对本专题广泛持有的意见进行数字整合的方法",
  "Dividing the equation into partial solutions when viewed through a simplified analytical lens": "在通过简化分析透镜观察时,将等式分为部分解决办法",
  "Splitting a rational expression into simpler fractions to facilitate integration, e.g., 1/(P(K-P)) = 1/K * [1/P + 1/(K-P)]": "将合理表达式分割成简单分数以促进整合,例如,1/(P(K-P))=1/K *[1/P+1/(K-P)]",
  "Factoring the denominator only without accounting for additional influences": "只在不考虑其他影响的情况下对分母进行乘数",
  "When solving the logistic equation by separation of variables, the left side becomes dP/[P(K-P)]. Partial fractions decompose this as (1/K)[1/P + 1/(K-P)], allowing each term to be integrated as a logarithm.": "在通过变量分离来解析后勤方程时,左侧成为dP/[P(K-P)]。部分分解成(1/K)[1/P+1/(K-P)],允许将每个术语合并为对数。",
  "What does 'maximum sustainable yield' mean?": "“最高可持续产量”意味着什么?",
  "The maximum harvesting rate that can be sustained indefinitely, equal to the maximum growth rate at P = K/2": "可无限期持续的最高收获率,相当于P=K/2的最高增长率",
  "The maximum number of individuals that can exist, which is a common assumption in the field": "能够存在的最多人数的个人人数,这是该领域的一个共同假设",
  "The carrying capacity K under most circumstances involving maintained": "在多数情况下涉及维持的承载能力",
  "The growth rate r given that prevailing maintained conditions tend to reinforce this particular": "增长率r ,因为普遍维持的状况往往使这一特别情况更加恶化。",
  "Maximum sustainable yield (MSY) is the largest harvest rate that can be maintained without depleting the population. In the logistic model, MSY = rK/4, which occurs when the population is maintained at K/2.": "最高可持续收成率(MSY)是可以保持的最大收成率,不消耗人口,在后勤模式中,MSY=rK/4,当人口保持K/2时即发生。",
  "What is the meaning of the 'logistic factor' (1 - P/K)?": "“后勤因素”(1-P/K)的含义是什么?",
  "The growth rate, at least according to standard theory": "增长率,至少根据标准理论",
  "The total resources available within the broader context of factor analysis": "在更广泛的要素分析范围内可动用的资源总额",
  "The fraction of the carrying capacity that remains available, which decreases as P approaches K": "由于P接近K而减少的剩余承载能力部分",
  "The probability of an individual surviving without accounting for additional influences": "个人在不考虑其他影响的情况下生存的概率",
  "The logistic factor (1 - P/K) represents the proportion of unused carrying capacity. When P is small compared to K, this factor is near 1 (growth is nearly unrestricted). When P approaches K, it approaches 0 (growth stalls).": "后勤系数(1-P/K)代表未使用的承载能力的比例。当P小于K时,这个系数接近1(增长几乎不受限制)。当P接近K时,它接近0(增长摊位)。",
  "What does 'separable form' of the logistic equation mean?": "后勤方程式的“可分离形式”意味着什么?",
  "Writing the equation with P and t on the same side": "以 P 和 t 写入同一边的方程式",
  "Expressing the equation as a linear function": "以线性函数表示等式",
  "Rewriting the equation as dP/[P(1-P/K)] = r dt so variables P and t are separated for integration": "将方程重写为 dP/[P(1-P/K)] = r dt, 这样变量P和 t就分开, 以便整合",
  "Separating the carrying capacity from the growth rate": "将承载能力与增长率分开",
  "The logistic equation is separable: dP/[P(1-P/K)] = r dt. All P-dependent terms are on the left, and the t-dependent terms are on the right, allowing integration of both sides.": "后勤方程式可以分开:dP/[P(1-P/K)]=rdt。 所有的P依赖条件在左边,T依赖条件在右边,允许双方合并。",
  "What is the 'point of diminishing returns' in logistic growth?": "后勤增长中“回报减少点”是什么?",
  "The point where P = 0": "P=0的点",
  "The point where growth first begins": "开始增长的起点",
  "The point where P = K": "P = K 的点点",
  "The inflection point at P = K/2 where the growth rate begins to decrease": "P=K/2的偏移点,增长率开始下降",
  "The point of diminishing returns is at P = K/2, where the growth rate starts to decline. Before this point, growth accelerates. After it, growth decelerates due to increasing density dependence.": "回报率下降的点是P = K/2, 其增长率开始下降。在此点之前, 增长会加速。 之后, 增长会因对密度的依赖性增加而减速 。",
  "What is an 'equilibrium analysis' of a logistic equation?": "后勤方程式的“平衡分析”是什么?",
  "Calculating the balance point of forces": "计算部队的平衡点",
  "Finding the constant solutions (where dP/dt = 0) and determining their stability": "寻找常数解决方案( dP/ dt = 0) 并确定其稳定性",
  "Setting all variables equal": "设置所有变量相等",
  "Finding the average value of P": "寻找 P 的平均值",
  "Equilibrium analysis identifies constant solutions by setting dP/dt = 0, finding P = 0 and P = K. Stability analysis then determines which are attractors (P = K is stable) and which are repellers (P = 0 is unstable for P > 0).": "平衡分析通过设定 dP/dt = 0, 找到 P = 0 和 P = K, 找出持续解决方案。 稳定分析然后确定哪些是吸引物( P = K 是稳定的),哪些是迁移者( P = 0 = P > 0 不稳定)。",
  "What does 'overshoot and oscillation' mean in population models?": "在人口模型中,“超射线和振荡”意味着什么?",
  "When the population grows indefinitely past K": "当人口无限期长过K",
  "When the population drops to zero": "当人口降到零时,",
  "When the growth rate oscillates between positive and negative": "当增长率在正与负之间波动时",
  "When a population exceeds its carrying capacity temporarily and may oscillate around K before stabilizing": "当一个人口暂时超过其承载能力时,在稳定之前,可能围绕K环绕K",
  "In the basic logistic model, there is no oscillation (approach to K is monotonic). However, in more complex models or discrete analogs, populations may overshoot K and oscillate before settling, especially with time delays.": "在基本后勤模式中,没有振荡(K对K的接近是单调的),但是,在较复杂的模型或离散模拟模型中,人口在安顿之前可能超过K和悬浮,特别是时间的拖延。",
  "What does 'phase line analysis' mean for the logistic equation?": "“阶段线分析”对后勤方程式意味着什么?",
  "Computing the phase angle of oscillation": "计算振动的相向角",
  "Analyzing the phases of the moon": "分析月亮的各个阶段,",
  "A one-dimensional diagram showing equilibria and the direction of population change along the P-axis": "一维图,显示P-轴线沿线人口平衡和变化方向",
  "Drawing the slope field in the tP-plane": "在 tP- 平面上绘制斜坡场",
  "Phase line analysis for dP/dt = f(P) plots P on a vertical axis, marks equilibria, and uses arrows to show the direction of change. For the logistic equation, arrows point up (increasing) for 0 < P < K and down (decreasing) for P > K.": "dP/dt = f(P) 垂直轴上的 P 绘图的阶段线分析,标记平衡,并使用箭头显示变化方向。对于后勤方程式,为 P > K 0 < P < K 向上( 递增) 和向下( 递减) 向上( 递增) 箭头指向 P > K 向下( 递减) 。",
  "A conservation officer manages a deer population following dP/dt = 0.2P(1 - P/3000). The current count is 1200 deer, and hunters request permits to harvest 150 deer per year. Is this sustainable?": "保护官员在DP/dt = 0.2P(1 - P/300)之后管理鹿群。 目前的计数是 1,200鹿,猎人每年申请150只鹿的捕捞许可证。 这可持续吗 ?",
  "No, it will cause extinction, since the prevailing theory about population would support this particular": "不,它将导致灭绝, 因为人口理论的流行 人口理论会支持这个特殊",
  "Yes; current growth rate is 0.2(1200)(0.6) = 144, and MSY = 0.2(3000)/4 = 150, so it is right at the maximum sustainable level": "是;目前的增长率为0.2(1200)(0.6)=144,而MSY=0.2(3,000/4)=150,因此在最高可持续水平是正确的",
  "Cannot be determined, particularly when population considerations are weighed against competing pressures": "无法确定,特别是当人口因素与相互竞争的压力相权衡时",
  "Yes, and they could harvest even more when viewed through a simplified analytical lens": "是的,如果通过简化的分析透镜来观察,它们可以收获更多",
  "MSY = rK/4 = 0.2(3000)/4 = 150. The requested harvest of 150 exactly equals the MSY. At the current population of 1200, growth is 144 < 150, so the population would slightly decline toward the lower equilibrium. This is marginally sustainable if the population is maintained at K/2 = 1500.": "MSY = rK/4 = 0.2(3000/4 = 150). 要求的150个收成完全等于 MSY。在目前的1200个人口中,人口增长率为144 < 150,因此人口将略微下降到较低平衡。如果人口保持K/2 = 1500,则人口略为可持续。",
  "A disease model uses dI/dt = 0.0005I(10000 - I) for infected individuals I. Write this in standard logistic form and find the time to reach 5000 infected if I(0) = 100.": "一种疾病模式对受感染者使用dI/dt = 0.0005I(1000 - I) = 0.0005I(1000 - I) 。",
  "t = 100 days, since the relevant infected factors typically produce this outcome in practice": "t = 100天,因为相关感染因素通常在实践中产生这种结果",
  "r = 5, K = 20000, as the dynamics involved tend to push conditions in this direction over time": "r = 5, K = 20000,因为所涉动态因素往往会随着时间的推移推动条件朝这个方向发展。",
  "r = 5, K = 10000; time = (1/5)ln(99*10000/5000) = (1/5)ln(99*2) -- but correct formula: t = (1/r)ln(A) where A = (K-P0)/P0 and P=K/2 gives t = ln(99)/5": "r = 5, K = 10000;时间 = (1/5ln(99*1000/500) = (1/5ln(99*2)) - 但正确的公式: t = (1/r)ln(A) A= (K-P0)/P0和P=K/2给 T = In(99)/5",
  "r = 0.0005, K = 10000 because the underlying forces at work tend to produce exactly this type of outcome": "r = 0.0005 K = 10000,因为工作的基本力量往往产生这种结果。",
  "dI/dt = 0.0005I(10000 - I) = 5 * I(1 - I/10000) (factoring 0.0005 * 10000 = 5). So r = 5, K = 10000. I(t) = 10000/(1 + 99e^(-5t)). At I = 5000: 2 = 1 + 99e^(-5t), e^(-5t) = 1/99, t = ln(99)/5 approximately 0.919 time units.": "dI/dt = 0.0005I(1000 - I) = 5 * I(1 - I/1000) = 5 * I(1 - I/1000) (计算单位:0.0005 * 100000 = 5) 所以 r = 5, K = 10000. I(t) = 1000/(1 + 99e* (5t)) 。 I = 5000: 2 = 1 + 99e(5t) , e(-5t) = 1/99, t = In(99)/5 约0.919个时间单位。",
  "A tech startup models user adoption with P(t) = 1,000,000/(1 + 999e^(-0.02t)). When does adoption reach 90% of the carrying capacity (900,000 users)?": "P(t) = 1 000 000/(1 + 999e(- 0.02t)) 的技术启动模式用户采用P(t) = 1 000 000/(1 + 999e(- 0.02t)) 的技术启动模式用户采用。 何时采用达到90%的承载能力(900 000用户)?",
  "t = 100 days, which is a common": "t = 100天,这是常见的",
